sogou-kaoyan.n: (per cent)百分比[出现17次)];分; 分值的硬币[出现0次)]

sogou-gaokao.adv/n: (per cent)百分之一; 百分比[出现1次)]

1.en: And 77 per cent said that any of the words used to say thanks were irrelevant, believing a pleasant gesture works just as well.
1.cn: 77%的人说用哪个词来表达谢谢都无所谓，他们相信一个亲切的动作能达到同样的效果。

2.en: Even more stunning was that, at the end of these two decades, 55 per cent of the workforce was at a new job.
2.cn: 更令人吃惊的是，在八九十年代末，55%的劳动力都在从事新的工作。

3.en: Despite the array of policies, national real estate prices have continued to rise, jumping 10. 7 per cent in February from a year earlier.
3.cn: 尽管出台了一系列政策，全国房地产价格仍继续上涨，2月份同比飙升10.

0.en: And I'm gonna sue you for every cent that you have ever made.
0.cn: 我会针对你过去挣的每一分钱进行起诉

1.en: Which means as the evening progresses we will get better looking99 cent Margaritas and two-for-one jello shot.
1.cn: 到了晚上我们就衣冠楚楚倾巢出动，99分一杯的玛格丽特，还有买一送一的果子冻饮料。

2.en: Well, it does seem rather ironic that for want of 99 cent adhesive ducks, we both might die in a fiery car crash.
2.cn: 因没买99美分的防滑鸭子而导致两个人都可能死于惨烈的车祸，这看上去真是非常讽刺。

3.en: I've spent every penny I've ever made trying to put you out of business. Except this one. My last penny. Besides, what can I do with one measly cent anyway?
3.cn: 我把所有钱都花在试图破坏你的生意上了。除了这个，我最后一个铜板。而且，我能拿这可怜的一分钱做什么呢？

4.en: Oh, I see. You don't have the money, do you? Well, we don't quite have it all locked in... Well, you'll not get a cent out of me.
4.cn: 哦，我知道了。你是手头没钱了，对不对？我们就差那么一点点……我是一个子都不会掏的。
